    <h3 class="post-title">
	 BlunderDome Disruption
    </h3>
	 
    

    <div class="post-body">

      <p>
      <div style="clear:both;"></div><p>I&rsquo;m consolidating all of the <a href="http://nfocentrale.com/">nfoCentrale</a> web sites (this blog is on&nbsp;one of them) on a single web hosting account at <a href="http://a2hosting.com/">A2 Hosting</a>.&nbsp; I have already moved&nbsp;most of my sites to that account, with only minor breakage around Apache case sensitivity.&nbsp;&nbsp;Sites that have blogs or that have&nbsp;e-mail accounts are trickier to move and I have saved those for last.&nbsp; Today, the movers are coming to Orcmid&rsquo;s Lair, the BlunderDome, and Professor von Clueless.&nbsp; And of course, neither last nor least, Spanner Wingnut&rsquo;s Muddleware Lab.</p><p align="center">{tags: <a href="http://www.technorati.com/tag/orcmid" rel="tag">orcmid</a> <a href="http://www.technorati.com/tag/A2+Hosting" rel="tag">A2 Hosting</a> <a href="http://www.technorati.com/tag/nfoCentrale" rel="tag">nfoCentrale </a><a href="http://www.technorati.com/tag/web+hosting" rel="tag">web hosting</a> <a href="http://www.technorati.com/tag/Apache" rel="tag">Apache</a> <a href="http://www.technorati.com/tag/system+incoherence" rel="tag">system incoherence</a> <a href="http://www.technorati.com/tag/confirmable+experience" rel="tag">confirmable experience</a>&nbsp;<a href="http://www.technorati.com/tag/Ed+Bott" rel="tag">Ed Bott</a>}</p><p>What this means for the readers of these blogs is that the best reception will be found at URLs like <a href="http://orcmid.com/BlunderDome/clueless">http://orcmid.com/BlunderDome/clueless</a> and <em>not</em> <a href="http://nfocentrale.net/orcmid/BlunderDome/clueless">http://nfocentrale.net/orcmid/BlunderDome/clueless</a>.&nbsp; In fact, the second URL and the&nbsp;site feed at the same location will be not see any more blog updates for several&nbsp;weeks.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;So what else is new, you say?&nbsp; Change to use the new location when I say &ldquo;ready&rdquo; over there and we&rsquo;ll see.</p><p>The Professor von Clueless&nbsp;blog and feed at <a href="http://orcmid.com/BlunderDome/clueless">http://orcmid.com/BlunderDome/clueless</a> will see little or no interruption.&nbsp; There may be&nbsp;some breakage,&nbsp;with templates, links, images, and archive&nbsp;pages having problems until the construction crew can straighten things out.&nbsp;</p><p>The longer-term benefit is that URLs like <a href="http://orcmid.com/">http://orcmid.com</a>&nbsp;will no longer&nbsp;forward to a different URL.&nbsp; Instead,&nbsp;all nfoCentrale sites will&nbsp;have full-size, grown-up, first-class, independent domains with sites to match.&nbsp;&nbsp; Now bookmarks made to pages found through orcmid.com follow the site wherever it may happen to be hosted in the future.</p><p>Well, what does all of this have to do with Spanner Wingnut?&nbsp; Naturally, this blog is the place where momentous changes to the nfoCentrale blogs are supposed to happen first.&nbsp; And that is how it will go.</p><p>First, the orcmid.com site (now showing at <a href="http://nfocentrale.net/orcmid">nfoCentrale.<strong>net</strong>/orcmid</a>) will be completely backed up, including all three blogs on that site: Orcmid&rsquo;s Lair, Professor von Clueless, and your humble Spanner Wingnut&rsquo;s Muddleware Lab.&nbsp; </p><p>All of that material will be dropped off at a new anchor site location, <a href="http://nfocentrale.com/orcmid">nfoCentrale.<strong>com</strong>/orcmid</a>.&nbsp; Yes indeed, I registered a new domain just to pull all of this off.&nbsp; And no, the orcmid directory isn&rsquo;t there just yet.&nbsp; Patience, pulleeeze.</p><p>Then, after nosing around to make sure nothing terribly bad happens in the new site (mainly related to case-sensitivity differences between Apache and the Microsoft Internet Information Server, IIS), orcmid.com will be hosted as its own full-fledged domain that happens to get its content from, ahem, <a href="http://orcmid.nfocentrale.com/">orcmid.nfocentrale.com</a> (also not there yet, but keep watching) which, if you haven&rsquo;t already guessed, gets its content from nfocentrale.com/orcmid.&nbsp; Tricky but effective.</p><p>I&rsquo;m so excited!&nbsp; I&rsquo;ve been waiting for years to accomplish what I just learned is called add-on domain hosting.&nbsp; And now I can.&nbsp; All because <a href="http://www.edbott.com/weblog/?p=1504">Ed Bott</a> gave a testimonial to <a href="http://www.a2hosting.com/">A2 Hosting</a> on his blog page.</p><div style="clear:both; padding-bottom: 0.25em;"></div>
    </p>

    </div>

    <p class="post-footer">
      <em>posted by orcmid @ <a href="http://orcmid.com/BlunderDome/wingnut/2006/10/blunderdome-disruption.asp" title="permanent link">10/11/2006 01:21:30 PM</a></em> &nbsp;
        
    </p>

  

